## How to install

This bundle is loaded by the Eliza desktop app and the Eliza mobile
clients. From the Eliza desktop app: open the **Models** panel, pick
the on-device tier matching this bundle (`{{ tier }}`), and press
install. The downloader resolves the manifest, fetches each file, and
verifies each `sha256` before activating the bundle.

For an operator-side direct download of the exact same phone/desktop
payload:

```bash
{{ hf_cli_download_command }}
```

Mobile clients resolve `{{ manifest_remote_path }}` first, then download
only the files declared in the manifest and validate every manifest
`sha256` against `{{ checksum_remote_path }}`.

The runtime activates this bundle iff every required kernel listed in
the manifest has a `pass` status on the user's verified backend. There
is no fallback to an unoptimized build — a bundle whose kernels do not
match the device is reported as incompatible.

